<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: DELAITTRE TRANSFERS TO VALLEY AFTER REDSHIRTING 1ST SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shawn DeLaittre, who helped lead Simi Valley High to the Southern Section 4-A 
Division basketball title in 1988, has transferred from Cal Poly San Luis 
Obispo to Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
DeLaittre, a forward who averaged 21.6 points and 8.8 rebounds a game during 
his senior season at Simi Valley, transferred to Valley after redshirting his 
freshman season at San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
Doug Block, 25, has been hired as defensive line and film coach for the Cal 
State Northridge grid team. 
</P>
<P>
Block worked with the defensive line at Southeast Missouri State last season. 
He previously had been a graduate assistant at Arkansas State, where he 
attended school and played football. 
</P>
<P>
Block replaces Jerry Campbell, the new football coach at St. Bernard High in 
Playa del Rey. 
</P>
<P>
Running back Albert Fann, linebacker Preston Hayslette, quarterback Sherdrick 
Bonner and tight end Richard Ane have been selected captains of the Cal State 
Northridge grid team by the players. 
</P>
<P>
The Philadelphia 76ers have signed former Cleveland High player Kevin Holmes to 
a one-year contract to play backup to forward Charles Barkley. Terms of the 
contract were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
Holmes, 24, was the 76ers' fifth-round draft pick in the 1986 NBA draft. For 
the past three years, he has played overseas for Pully, Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
Last season, the 6-foot-8 Holmes averaged 25 points and 10 rebounds. His team 
won the Swiss league, playoffs and Swiss Cup. 
</P>
<P>
The Burbank Hilton Sure Shots captured the American Softball Assn. Women's Fast 
Pitch B national championship Sunday in Tucson, Ariz., with a 4-3 victory over 
Joe's Unocal of Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
Kim Powers of the University of Indiana, a 1987 graduate of Burroughs High in 
Burbank, was named tournament MVP. 
</P>
