<P>
The Bulgarian government accused Turkey of playing "a dirty political game" 
with its decision requiring that ethnic Turks immigrating from Bulgaria first 
obtain visas. However, the semiofficial Turkish news agency Anatolia said 522 
ethnic Turks were allowed to cross without visas. The refugees say they are 
fleeing a harsh assimilation campaign. The Turkish government announced its 
move Monday, saying it would require the visas because Bulgaria's Communist 
leaders have refused to start talks on an accord to protect the emigrants. 
Turkish officials said the border will stay closed until Sofia signs an 
emigration pact with Ankara safeguarding the rights of ethnic Turks wanting to 
emigrate and of those staying behind. 
