<HEADLINE>
<P>
'HUSH PUPPIES' PLAYSUITS RECALLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A New Jersey company is recalling 47,000 "Hush Puppies" sweat suits for 
children because a noisemaking device behind the plastic dog decal on the suit 
can come loose and present a choking hazard, the Consumer Product Safety 
Commission said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the suits were supplied by The Haddad Group Ltd. of 
Bayonne, N.J., and were sold at Montgomery Ward stores from August until 
mid-December, 1988. No injuries have been reported. 
</P>
<P>
The suits may be returned to any Montgomery Ward store or mailed to The Haddad 
Group Ltd., 90 East 5th St., Bayonne, N.J., 07002, for a full refund plus 
postage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082389-0067 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 98203 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 23, 1989, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
