<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTOPSIES SCHEDULED ON 2 SLAYING VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Autopsies were expected to be conducted today on the bodies of entertainment 
executive Jose Menendez and his wife, who were slain Sunday night in their 
Beverly Hills mansion. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Dambacher, a spokesman for the Los Angeles County coroner, said the 
autopsies on Menendez, 45, and his wife, Mary Louise (Kitty) Menendez, 44, 
could provide information on how the couple were shot to death. 
</P>
<P>
The Beverly Hills Police Department has declined to comment on its 
investigation of the shootings. Officials will not say whether there are any 
suspects in the case. 
</P>
<P>
Also, police will not describe the weapon with which the couple were shot 
several times. 
</P>
<P>
"We are looking into many aspects in this case," said police spokesman Lt. 
Robert Curtis. "Whether it's robbery or revenge or business-related, we don't 
know. There are many possible avenues." 
</P>
<P>
Menendez, chief executive officer and chairman of LIVE Entertainment Inc. of 
Van Nuys, a video and production firm, once headed RCA/Ariola records as well 
as U.S. rental car operations for Hertz Corp. 
</P>
<P>
Approximately 49% of LIVE's stock is owned by Los Angeles-based Carolco 
Pictures, which has produced actor Sylvester Stallone's Rambo films. 
</P>
</TEXT>
