<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOPHOMORE SAFETY IS LATEST ADDITION TO USC INJURY LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With its season opener still nearly two weeks away, the USC football team is 
battling a more immediate problem -- injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Doctors determined Tuesday that backup safety Lamont Hollinquest has a ruptured 
tendon in his left ring finger. The injury, which occurred last week, is 
expected to sideline the sophomore from four to five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Out from four to six weeks is fullback Raoul Spears after arthroscopic surgery 
for torn cartilage in his right knee. 
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, the team lost starting nose guard Don Gibson for six to eight 
weeks because of torn ligaments in his left knee. 
</P>
<P>
The team will practice at UC Irvine through Saturday, then return to USC to 
prepare for its Sept. 4 opener against Illinois. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
