<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jimmy (The Greek) Snyder is returning to television. Snyder, who lost his job 
with CBS sports 19 months ago after telling an interviewer blacks were better 
athletes than whites because they were bred for strength during slavery, will 
handicap pro football games this seasons for FNN's sports network. Snyder will 
appear Saturday and Sunday nights on "Who Beat the Spread," a live football 
analysis show, the cable network said Tuesday. The longtime handicapper, who 
was part of CBS' "NFL Today" on-air team for 12 years, has been away from 
television since his controversial statements, except for a show he did on the 
NCAA basketball tournament for Black Entertainment Television. 
</P>
</TEXT>
