<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the first of several moves planned by NBC Sports President Dick Ebersol, the 
new overseer of NBC News' "Today" show, Deborah Norville and veteran NBC 
newsman John Palmer will switch jobs, with Palmer moving from anchoring news 
reports of "Today" to those of "NBC News at Sunrise," and Norville from 
"Sunrise" to Palmer's "Today" post. NBC said Tuesday that the change, in which 
Norville also will do feature reporting and regularly fill in for vacationing 
"Today" co-anchors, is effective Sept. 5. 
</P>
