<HEADLINE>
<P>
BANGLADESH TIGERS KILL 7 WOODCUTTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAKA, Bangladesh 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tigers killed seven woodcutters and attacked about 20 other people this month 
in a mangrove forest in southern Bangladesh, officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Tigers have killed 70 people so far this year, according to official figures. 
Villagers said the toll is probably higher because many poachers hunting tigers 
haven't returned. 
</P>
<P>
Poaching has increased despite a 1982 ban on hunting the 600 remaining Bengal 
tigers and other rare animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
