UC IRVINE NOTES; 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER TEAM BEGINS PLAY SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UC Irvine men's soccer team will start the season at 3 p.m. Saturday with 
an exhibition game at Westmont College in Santa Barbara. Irvine also will play 
an exhibition game at Cal Poly Pomona at 3 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine has 13 players back from last year's team that finished with a 7-12 
overall record, finishing in fifth place in the Big West Conference. 
</P>
<P>
The most notable returning player is senior midfielder Darren Bedolla, a 
first-team All-Big West selection in 1988. Bedolla led the Anteaters in scoring 
last year with five goals and six assists. 
</P>
<P>
The Irvine women's volleyball team will play an varsity-alumni match Thursday 
at 6 p.m. in Crawford Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine will participate in the All-Cal scrimmage tournament Aug. 30 at UCLA. 
The Anteaters will participate in pool play against UC San Diego at 11 a.m., 
UCLA at 12:15 p.m., Berkeley at 2:30, UC Davis at 3:45 and UC Riverside at 5. 
Each scrimmage match is best-of-three instead of the regular best-of-five 
format. 
</P>
