<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Postal Service Cuts Jobs: The Postal Service said it is eliminating 1,000 
managerial and administrative positions at 39 facilities nationwide in a 
consolidation move. The agency said the cuts will have no effect on mail 
service. The consolidation, which takes effect Sept. 23, is expected to save 
$30 million to $35 million a year, the Postal Service said. Jobs will be 
eliminated through early retirements and other forms of attrition, postal 
officials said. In California, three management sectional centers are to be 
eliminated in Pasadena, Redding and Marysville. 
</P>
