</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 2,000 East Germans have escaped to the West through Hungary the last 
four days and sought refuge in West Germany, a Foreign Ministry source said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
The source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said that so far this month 
about 3,300 East Germans had illegally left their country. The refugees have 
overwhelmed West Germany's embassies abroad and threatened its relations with 
Communist East Berlin. 
</P>
<P>
The source said 2,000 East Germans who escaped via Austria between Saturday and 
Tuesday have applied to the West German Embassy in Vienna for travel documents. 
</P>
