<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
LSU FULLBACK WILLIAMS SUSPENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BATON ROUGE, La. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Louisiana State fullback Darrell Williams has been suspended for three games 
because of a bar fight that sent two men to a hospital, Coach Mike Archer said. 
</P>
<P>
Archer said Williams was at fault for the incident outside the Tiger bar, which 
led to his suspension from the games against Texas A&amp;M, Florida State and 
Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
According to a police report, Williams got into an argument and then a fight 
with Ray P. Fitch, 21, of Baton Rouge and a man identified only as Darrin 
Kimble. It said Fitch and Kimble both went to Our Lady of the Lake Hospital, 
where they were treated and released. Both told police at the time that they 
planned to press charges against Williams, but both said Tuesday that they were 
dropping the matter. Williams said he agreed to pay the hospital bills of the 
two men. 
</P>
</TEXT>
